Rick Perry has risked fanning the flames of criticism for his handling of the Texas wildfires by failing to show for a pre-arranged press conference.

The Texas governor and Republican presidential nominee was scheduled to be in Bastrop on Saturday to see and talk about the latest on the huge blazes, which have torched 1,600 homes and killed four people.

But he didn't turn up.

