Governor Rick Perry's office said families whose homes have been destroyed will receive seven-day hotel vouchers from a non-profit organisation as well as assistance from the state.

The vouchers were welcome relief for Russell Horn, who said the $104 nightly hotel bill for him, his wife and two boys had become too costly.

The 32-year-old electrician said their home had been destroyed by the fire and he had only been able to get out wearing an undershirt and shorts.

‘There aren't too many places you can go just wearing that,’ Mr Horn said.

